            <title>[DERBY-1814] Tests should always be compiled with line number information.</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/DERBY-1814</link>
                <project id="10594" key="DERBY">Derby</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Currently compiling in insane modes means that the tests do not have line number information, this makes investigating test failures harder.&lt;br/&gt;
